<subsection xml:id="subsec-speed-and-velocity" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Speed and Velocity</title>
    <objectives component="outcomes">
        <introduction xml:id="auto_dtquue1s">
            <dl>
                <li xml:id="auto_saovtpbu">
                    <title>Strand</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_lv6gsyzl">
                        2.0 Measurements and Geometry
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_dlaraz8l">
                    <title>Sub-Strand</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_866d02bp">
                        2.10 Linear Motion
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_3fmim6jb">
                    <title>Specific Learning Outcomes</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_4jayc4ri">
                        Explain the terms speed and velocity in real-life situations and determine velocity in different situations.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_hj6nhli5" component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Grade Level</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_6f1ij1sl">
                        10
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_owi252eh" component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Estimated Duration</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_7fgttw25">
                        40 minutes
                    </p>
                </li>
            </dl>
            <p xml:id="auto_9ifyzxr7" component="lesson-plan">
                <p xml:id="auto_xxfckhod"> Upon completion of this lesson, learners will be able to:
                <ol>
                    <li xml:id="auto_wi5mld5e">
                        <p xml:id="auto_ygi4yane">
                            <alert>Know (Conceptual Understanding):</alert> Define speed as the rate of change of distance with time (scalar) and velocity as speed in a specified direction or the rate of change of displacement with time (vector). Understand the difference between average speed and average velocity.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_8exo3huh">
                        <p xml:id="auto_uba7ikur">
                            <alert>Do (Procedural Skill):</alert> Apply the formulas for average speed (<m>\text{speed} = \frac{\text{distance}}{\text{time}}</m>) and average velocity (<m>v = \frac{\text{displacement}}{\text{time}}</m>) to solve problems involving multi-segment journeys.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_9vgj1x4j">
                        <p xml:id="auto_gkpq8luh">
                            <alert>Apply (Application/Problem-Solving):</alert> Solve real-world problems involving speed and velocity such as travel journeys with rest stops, multi-segment trips, and situations where direction matters.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
                </p>
            </p>
        </introduction>
    </objectives>
    <axiom component="resources">
        <!-- Link to blurb -->
        <xi:include href="../../resources-blurb-lesson.ptx" />

        <sbsgroup widths="45% 45%" margins="2% 2%">
            <sidebyside>
                <p xml:id="auto_rhg5lobt">
                    <dataurl source="lesson_plans/measurements-and-geometry/linear-motion/speed-and-velocity.pdf"> Lesson Plan </dataurl>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_u0ukeupz">
                    <dataurl source="lesson_plans/measurements-and-geometry/linear-motion/step-by-step-guide_speed-and-velocity.pdf"> Step-by-Step Guide </dataurl>
                </p>
            </sidebyside>
        </sbsgroup>
    </axiom>
    <xi:include href="../../resources-materials.ptx" />

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Phase 1: Rolling Ball Experiment and Walking in Opposite Directions</title>
        <dl>
            <li xml:id="auto_mcasr7lm">
                <title>Suggested Time</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_oy8gpj9c">
                    15 minutes
                </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_m20hs50z">
                <title>Grouping</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_7lxrx4e5">
                    Work in small groups (3<ndash/>4 students)
                </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_yooz9t5j">
                <title>Materials</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_ylve0ggk">
                    Stopwatch, measuring tape, ball or round object, chalk/tape to mark positions, open space (classroom or field)
                </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_736qrgh7">
                <title>Teacher's Role</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_1s9jrbrr">
                    Guide students through both activities. For the rolling ball experiment, ensure students measure distances and times accurately. For the walking activity, help students set up the central point and mark 10 m east and west. After both activities, ask probing questions to elicit the difference between speed and velocity.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_sdchza7k">
                <title>Discussion Questions</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_ger25yqv">
                    <ol marker="(a)">
                        <li xml:id="auto_4qo82rms"><p xml:id="auto_jhnmygkv"><q>Both students walked the same distance. Is their velocity the same? Why or why not?</q></p></li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_io6z7l8h"><p xml:id="auto_lhyyw1xk"><q>What is the difference between speed and velocity?</q></p></li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_7oc81eik"><p xml:id="auto_n88wxai5"><q>If a car drives in a circle and returns to its starting point, what is its average velocity?</q></p></li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_usmi0eup"><p xml:id="auto_vfflmg6m"><q>Can average speed ever equal zero? Can average velocity equal zero?</q></p></li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </li>
        </dl>
        <p xml:id="auto_ikqvnooy">
            Identify 2<ndash/>3 groups with clear findings to share with the class.
        </p>
    </axiom>
    <activity xml:id="auto_h6mn155j">
        <p xml:id="auto_3mewiecp">
            <alert>Work in groups</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_07xj75zg">
            <alert>Materials:</alert> Stop watch, Measuring tape and ball/round object 
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_hbxkhmsc">
            <ol xml:id="auto_dn9d9xmm" marker="i).">
                <li xml:id="auto_fmc41r8m">
                    <p xml:id="auto_s7u475hr">
                        Roll a ball or any round object on the table 
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_o5qv37r1">
                    <p xml:id="auto_zew8i2f4">
                        Measure the rolling distance using the tape measure
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_yezk4odq">
                    <p xml:id="auto_9hs778yu">
                        Record the time when rolling
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_bnprfi5f">
                    <p xml:id="auto_kbksijqv">
                        Find the speed of the rolling ball
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </activity>
