                        <li xml:id="auto_5va7uaew"><p xml:id="auto_a60rsrtw">Total distance <m>= 100</m> km. Total time <m>= 2.5</m> hours. Average speed <m>= \frac{100}{2.5} = 40</m> km/h.</p></li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_omp7guez"><p xml:id="auto_s8jtrm4z">Average speed <m>= \frac{400}{80} = 5</m> m/s. Average velocity <m>= 0</m> m/s (displacement is zero).</p></li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_vudg4tk7"><p xml:id="auto_grr3xbhw">Speed tells how fast; velocity tells how fast and in what direction.</p></li>
